main event: Observation of a bright light object over Pebble Beach, California on April 3, 1961.
interesting points: The object was detected by ground-radar and air-intercept radar,The object exhibited extremely rapid maneuvers with an estimated speed of Mach 10-12,The observer indicated the object made a maneuver and disappeared, only to be lost from the radar afterward, The sighting lasted approximately 15 minutes, The observer was able to visualize the object alongside radar detection.
sighted object: a bright light object resembling a star with a ring of light
